{
  "stem": "10905.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was it, the deprivation of food, not having anything to do.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now interestingly enough, and I think this never happened to anybody during the entire war is that they allowed us to empty out the hospital barrack, and we had, in fact, Rosh Hashanah and Yom Kippur services.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Which, I don't think ever happened before or after in any of the other concentration camps any group of people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] One day in November-- from time to time there would be Red Cross parcels of cigarettes, I think, that they were distributing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And with cigarettes, you could trade.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In those days everybody was smoking.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "With cigarettes it was like today you have Swiss francs or dollars.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You could trade anything for cigarettes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I have to tell you about my mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My mother was a very beautiful lady.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And no matter what happened throughout, she had firstly, we were terrors, my sister and I.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she would say not my children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My children are the  most wonderful children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the second thing, she had a tiny little piece of broken mirror and the lipstick.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she just had to put her lipstick on and look as if she were-- wherever she was going.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Everybody, they had, obviously, we were not the first people in that compound.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So people would initial their names and dates and write names into the compounds.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "One day, my mother in November gets a dream that something wonderful is going to happen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Sure enough, 10 days later, they start giving us food.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Much greater rations and much different and much better rations than we'd ever had.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was at the end of November of 1944.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
